he's going through.

35:31.996 --> 35:35.299
Did you ever have
appendicitis?
No.

35:35.366 --> 35:38.803
Do you know that when someone
has it, they have a hell
of a lot of pain?

35:38.869 --> 35:41.572
You know,
I was so busy telling
David and his parents...

35:41.639 --> 35:46.911
not to expect too much
on the first visit,
I-I forgot to tell myself.

35:46.978 --> 35:51.749
I guess now I'm feeling
his depression
and disappointment.

35:51.816 --> 35:55.319
You know, Phil,

35:55.386 --> 35:59.657
the mind can play
dangerous Tricks.

35:59.724 --> 36:04.228
Your conscious self knows
that you're doing the best
you can to treat this boy.

36:04.295 --> 36:07.932
But the subconscious?
Ah, the subconscious
is like a computer.

36:07.999 --> 36:12.837
It can't make judgments
about right or wrong.
It just stores facts.

36:12.903 --> 36:15.973
And the fact is...

36:16.040 --> 36:18.409
that no matter
how hard it gets,

36:18.476 --> 36:22.647
David Steward is trying
to find himself through you.

36:24.181 --> 36:26.984
Yeah.
That's pretty good, Beale.

36:27.051 --> 36:28.986
Just common sense.

36:29.053 --> 36:34.358
You know, I didn't realize
I'm David's chance
for recovery.

36:34.425 --> 36:36.527
I just thought I was
another spoke in the wheel.

36:36.594 --> 36:39.897
You would have reached
the same conclusion
on your own eventually.

36:39.964 --> 36:42.366
Even if you did
go to Yale.

36:48.539 --> 36:53.611
<i>Dr. Chandler?
Oh, hello.
How are you?</i>

36:53.678 --> 36:56.714
I might have some information
about the word Sterling.

36:56.781 --> 37:00.518
I don't know if it's too
valuable, but you did say
to let you know anything,

37:00.584 --> 37:02.653
no matter how insignificant
it might be.

37:02.720 --> 37:06.090
Yes, please, go ahead.
Well, I talked
to David's grandmother,

37:06.157 --> 37:09.360
and it seems that
when David was about 10 or 11,

37:09.427 --> 37:12.930
he bought his mother
a Sterling silver
St. Christopher Medal.

37:12.997 --> 37:15.166
Well, was that
a big thing to him?
It was.

37:15.232 --> 37:18.803
It seems that he worked
at the corner grocery store
for about a month,

37:18.869 --> 37:21.539
just running errands
so that he'd have enough
money to pay for it.

37:21.606 --> 37:24.241
What happened to it?
After his mother died,

37:24.308 --> 37:27.545
Michael gave it back to him
so that he could have it
as a keepsake.

37:27.612 --> 37:32.249
Oh, okay. Well, thank you.
Thank you. Maybe that'll help.

37:37.955 --> 37:40.458
Get up.

37:40.524 --> 37:44.495
Wake up. I gotta ask you
a few questions.
I'm tired.

37:44.562 --> 37:46.731
Look, you slept all afternoon.
You missed physical Therapy.

37:46.797 --> 37:48.866
Come on, let's go.
It's that drug
you gave me.

37:48.933 --> 37:51.569
Baloney.
Low-Dose sedatives
don't make you that sleepy.

37:55.273 --> 37:58.042
Okay. Now.

38:00.177 --> 38:04.382
You bought your mother
a Sterling silver
St. Christopher medal.

38:04.448 --> 38:07.618
And when she died,
your father gave it back
to you. Do you remember?

38:07.685 --> 38:10.921
Nope.
Try. It was five
or six years ago.

38:10.988 --> 38:13.891
You saved up the money
by getting a job
at a local grocery store.

38:13.958 --> 38:15.893
Sorry, I can't.
Think.

38:15.960 --> 38:17.328
I am.
No, you're not.

38:17.395 --> 38:19.764
I said I can't remember.
You're not trying.

38:19.830 --> 38:23.100
Think. Try. Remember.
Talk, talk, talk.

38:23.167 --> 38:25.569
I'm tired of it.
I've had enough.
Just concentrate.

38:25.636 --> 38:27.939
I'm tired of it!

38:28.005 --> 38:30.775
Look, David,
I can't help you
if you won't let me.

38:30.841 --> 38:33.044
I don't want your help.
It won't do any good.

38:33.110 --> 38:36.614
I'm gonna be this way forever,
so stop wasting your time, okay?

38:40.384 --> 38:42.787
I know what's wrong
with Mr. Heller.

38:42.853 --> 38:46.324
Heller?
Oh, the nosebleed?
Gaucher's disease.

38:46.390 --> 38:49.860
Go-Shay's.
Yeah.

38:49.927 --> 38:54.465
Well, you've gone
from a basic nosebleed
to a rare, chronic disease.

38:54.532 --> 38:59.470
One of probably 30 possibilities
for a bleeding disorder
and Splenomegaly.

38:59.537 --> 39:03.541
Listen. This is Arnold toynbee
on the migration
of the ashkenazim.

39:03.608 --> 39:07.111
Toynbee? The historian?
"The latter day
jewish herodians...

39:07.178 --> 39:09.547
"Seized the opportunity that
western liberalism offered,

39:09.614 --> 39:11.649
by carrying forward
the policy of assimilation."

39:11.716 --> 39:13.818
If you're gonna tell me
that gaucher's...

39:13.884 --> 39:17.588
is as common among
the ashkenazim as tay-Sachs,
I already know it.

39:17.655 --> 39:20.725
Now, Wendy, I think
your speculation
is very interesting.

39:20.791 --> 39:23.794
I really do. But toynbee
isn't medical fact, is it?

39:23.861 --> 39:27.598
<i>What's your diagnosis?
Heavy and spontaneous
bleeding from the nose.</i>

39:27.665 --> 39:30.167
Pain of varying severity
in the knees, hips
and Shoulders.

39:30.234 --> 39:33.037
<i>Bruises. A protruding abdomen
because of an enlarged spleen
and liver.</i>

39:33.104 --> 39:36.474
Member of a racial group prone
to a particular disease.

39:36.540 --> 39:38.542
I want to order
a glucocerebrosidase.

39:38.609 --> 39:40.678
That's
a very expensive test.

39:40.745 --> 39:42.580
It's the only way
I'll find out for sure.

39:42.647 --> 39:45.383
<i>It costs $250.
I realize that.</i>

39:45.449 --> 39:48.486
You do? Well, then
why don't you go ahead
and try it.

40:06.871 --> 40:10.007
- [ knocking ]
- What can I do for you?

40:10.074 --> 40:12.843
I do wanna Remember.

40:28.326 --> 40:31.062
Hi, Bob.
Mm.

40:31.128 --> 40:33.264
Oh, mark.
Shh.

40:34.432 --> 40:36.500
You were right,
you know.

40:36.567 --> 40:38.803
You can't make
new old friends.

40:41.405 --> 40:44.108
You're a good person, Bob.

40:44.175 --> 40:47.912
You always were,
and I know you always will be.

40:49.347 --> 40:53.451
So, I just
wanted to say, um,
good luck, Buddy.

41:25.816 --> 41:28.953
I don't know how...

41:29.020 --> 41:32.823
you can drink cold beer
when it is freezing outside.

41:32.890 --> 41:34.892
You know, it's gonna
get down to zero tonight?

41:34.959 --> 41:38.262
Yeah, I heard.
Why don't you put it
over here?

41:38.329 --> 41:40.264
I have an electric blanket
if you'd like.

41:40.331 --> 41:42.633
No, this is fine.

42:05.289 --> 42:07.892
I've always needed
someone like you.

42:10.494 --> 42:12.730
I've dreamed of someone
like you.

42:18.502 --> 42:20.438
When you went
to see Myra today--

42:20.504 --> 42:23.007
I just went to pick up
a few things.

42:29.447 --> 42:31.349
Feel my heart, Peter.

42:39.256 --> 42:41.158
Feel it.

42:47.665 --> 42:50.868
Valium and everything,
it still won't stop.

42:50.935 --> 42:55.506
Sandy, you have
nothing to worry about.

43:06.617 --> 43:08.519
Move in with me.

43:13.090 --> 43:15.893
I'll make you the happiest man
on the face of the earth.

43:19.930 --> 43:22.934
Please.
Come here.

43:26.671 --> 43:29.173
[ David ]
they said she was my mother.

43:29.240 --> 43:32.877
<i>[ Chandler ]
what do you say?
I think she was.</i>

43:33.978 --> 43:36.414
When I was supposedly dead,

43:36.480 --> 43:40.584
and I could see Fiscus
and the others working on me
in the emergency room?

43:40.651 --> 43:43.187
Yes?

43:43.254 --> 43:45.556
When I floated up
into the light,

43:47.224 --> 43:51.729
this is the woman
who held out her arms
and asked me if I was ready.

43:54.799 --> 43:58.002
Do you have
any other memories of her?

43:58.069 --> 44:00.204
<i>I've been trying to.
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>

44:03.040 --> 44:05.309
look at the photograph.

44:07.178 --> 44:09.580
Concentrate on her face.

44:16.587 --> 44:18.556
Study it.

44:21.425 --> 44:23.394
Sit back, relax.

44:28.432 --> 44:30.635
See her face Smiling.

44:31.802 --> 44:33.804
Imagine the smile
getting wider and wider,

44:33.871 --> 44:37.241
until it breaks
into a laugh.

44:37.308 --> 44:40.344
Can you see her laughing?

44:40.411 --> 44:42.346
Yeah.
Okay.

44:42.413 --> 44:44.315
Good.

44:45.816 --> 44:48.719
Imagine yourself
in the photograph,

44:48.786 --> 44:51.255
Standing right next
to her, okay?

44:51.322 --> 44:53.524
And you're laughing too.

44:53.591 --> 44:58.863
You're sharing a joke together.
You're talking together.

45:00.898 --> 45:03.301
I see it.
Good.

45:04.368 --> 45:07.505
You take out
a brightly wrapped box,

45:07.571 --> 45:10.274
a gift for her.

45:10.341 --> 45:14.979
Imagine the color and design
of the wrapping paper.

45:15.046 --> 45:18.282
And a bow?
Oh, yeah, sure.
If you see it, yes.

45:19.317 --> 45:21.385
How big is the box?

45:21.452 --> 45:25.122
Well, it's not very big.
About, uh--

45:25.189 --> 45:29.493
<i>[ paper Rustling ]
about this big.</i>

45:29.560 --> 45:31.495
And you hand it
to her proudly.

45:31.562 --> 45:35.433
And she puts her arms
around you gratefully.

45:35.499 --> 45:38.369
But she hasn't
even opened it.

45:38.436 --> 45:43.207
Oh, she's-She's
happy to get it.

45:43.274 --> 45:45.710
It's a sign
of your love for her.

45:45.776 --> 45:48.412
And she loves you
very much.

45:50.548 --> 45:52.516
Open it.
Yes.

45:52.583 --> 45:57.722
Slowly she unfolds the bow,
pulls back the tape.

45:57.788 --> 46:01.392
See, she doesn't want to
mess up the wrapping paper.

46:01.459 --> 46:04.829
Takes out the little box.
Oh!

46:04.895 --> 46:08.633
She sees the name
of a jeweler on the top.

46:08.699 --> 46:11.102
Her eyes filled
with Expectation.

46:11.168 --> 46:15.306
She takes off the top,
looks inside.

46:15.373 --> 46:18.209
Great expectation
in her eyes.

46:19.977 --> 46:21.879
She pulls out this.

46:34.725 --> 46:37.662
<i>Scar.
Yes.</i>

46:40.798 --> 46:43.000
He had a scar.

46:43.067 --> 46:45.236
Who?

46:45.303 --> 46:48.406
The man.
The one who shot me.

46:48.472 --> 46:51.876
I-I--

46:51.943 --> 46:56.247
he took everything I had.

46:56.314 --> 47:00.818
I-I asked him,
I said,

47:00.885 --> 47:05.756
"Take my wallet, my watch,
but please leave me the medal."

47:12.863 --> 47:14.799
I remember.

47:19.303 --> 47:21.939
I remember the Scar.

47:27.545 --> 47:30.815
[ chuckling ]
[ sighs ]

47:33.784 --> 47:36.654
<i>[ knocking ]
come in.</i>

47:37.722 --> 47:39.657
Dr. Westphall?
Uh-huh.

47:39.724 --> 47:42.460
The special chemistry lab
completed the enzyme test
on Mr. Heller.

47:42.526 --> 47:46.330
He's got a glucocerebrosidase
level of 220.
That's very high.

47:46.397 --> 47:50.034
Not if you've got
gaucher's disease.
True enough.

47:50.101 --> 47:54.572
I was right.
Well, I wouldn't be
so happy about it.

47:54.639 --> 47:57.375
It's a chronic disease
and you're still gonna
have to tell Mr. Heller...

47:57.441 --> 47:59.777
that he's gonna
require medication
for the rest of his life.

47:59.844 --> 48:03.214
But I found it. It took me
all day and all night,
but I found it.

48:03.281 --> 48:05.616
Maybe next time
you'll do what I tell you to do.

48:05.683 --> 48:07.785
What do you mean?
What I told
you this morning.

48:07.852 --> 48:11.555
Get a complete
family history.

48:11.622 --> 48:14.725
Good night,
Dr. Westphall.
Good night.

48:14.792 --> 48:16.794
<i>Dr. Armstrong?</i>

48:18.496 --> 48:20.598
Congratulations.

49:02.640 --> 49:04.275
[ mews ]
